Funcom cries for help<br>
<br>
a consulting-company has been hired to take care of a large part of the game<br>
<br>
Funcom seems to have realized that the job of running the huge game has gone over their heads. Yesteday (18/10) they hired a consultant company to help them run the game. The tasks Funcom need help for are:<br>
<br>
        -creating friendlier, less formal connections to the community<br>
        - lowering response time for e-mail and in-game questions        <br>
        - Creating better tools for the supprt team, so they can solve problems for the players<br>
        - Expanding the Event part  to kick off the AO storyline        <br>
        - Moving towards a &quot;no surprises&quot;-philosophy, regarding telling players beforehand about         corrections and changes<br>
        - prioritizing the development efforts so that the bugs, that are most destructive to players         are fixed first        <br>
<br>
To us it sounds a bit like Themis Group, the consultant, will be running most of AO for Funcom. It must fell like a complete admission of failure for Funcom, who since the lauch have been struggling with exactly the parts they have now handed over to THemis Group. The could have done that 2 months ago.<br>
